{"action": "input", "code": "def find_squares_on_left_and_upper_left(grid: np.ndarray, s: Tuple[int, int]) -> Tuple[Tuple[int, int], Tuple[int, int]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Finds the squares on the left and upper left corner of the given square s in the given grid.\n\n    Args:\n    - grid (np.ndarray): A 2D numpy array representing the input grid.\n    - s (Tuple[int, int]): A tuple of integers (i, j) representing the indices of the square s.\n\n    Returns:\n    - A tuple of tuples ((i1, j1), (i2, j2)) representing the indices of the squares on the left and upper left corner of s.\n    \"\"\"\n    s1 = (s[0], s[1] - 1) if s[1] > 0 else None\n    s2 = (s[0] - 1, s[1] - 1) if s[0] > 0 and s[1] > 0 else None\n    return (s1, s2)\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    output_grid = np.copy(input_grid)\n    s = find_square_with_fewest_colored_dots(output_grid)\n    s1, s2 = find_squares_on_left_and_upper_left(output_grid)\n    output_grid = surround_squares_with_s1(output_grid, s, s1)\n    output_grid = surround_squares_with_s2(output_grid, s, s2)\n    return output_grid\ndef surround_squares_with_s1(grid: np.ndarray, s: Tuple[int, int], s1: Tuple[int, int]) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Surrounds the top, bottom, left, and right squares of all square s with s1.\n\n    Args:\n    - grid (np.ndarray): A 2D numpy array representing the input grid.\n    - s (Tuple[int, int]): A tuple of integers (i, j) representing the indices of the square s.\n    - s1 (Tuple[int, int]): A tuple of integers (i, j) representing the indices of the square s1.\n\n    Returns:\n    - A 2D numpy array representing the updated grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    i, j = s\n    i1, j1 = s1\n    if i > 0:\n        grid[i - 1, j] = i1\n    if i < grid.shape[0] - 1:\n        grid[i + 1, j] = i1\n    if j > 0:\n        grid[i, j - 1] = j1\n    if j < grid.shape[1] - 1:\n        grid[i, j + 1] = j1\n    return grid\ndef surround_squares_with_s2(grid: np.ndarray, s: Tuple[int, int], s2: Tuple[int, int]) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Surrounds the upper left, lower left, lower right, upper right, lower right of all squares s with s2.\n\n    Args:\n    - grid (np.ndarray): A 2D numpy array representing the input grid.\n    - s (Tuple[int, int]): A tuple of integers (i, j) representing the indices of the square s.\n    - s2 (Tuple[int, int]): A tuple of integers (i, j) representing the indices of the square s2.\n\n    Returns:\n    - A 2D numpy array representing the updated grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    i, j = s\n    i2, j2 = s2\n    if i > 0 and j > 0:\n        grid[i - 1, j - 1] = i2\n    if i < grid.shape[0] - 1 and j > 0:\n        grid[i + 1, j - 1] = i2\n    if i < grid.shape[0] - 1 and j < grid.shape[1] - 1:\n        grid[i + 1, j + 1] = i2\n    if i > 0 and j < grid.shape[1] - 1:\n        grid[i - 1, j + 1] = i2\n    grid[i, j] = i2\n    return grid\ndef find_square_with_fewest_colored_dots(grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[int, int]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Finds the square with the fewest colored dots in the given grid.\n\n    Args:\n    - grid (np.ndarray): A 2D numpy array representing the input grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    - A tuple of integers (i, j) representing the indices of the square with the fewest colored dots.\n    \"\"\"\n    min_dots = float('inf')\n    min_square = None\n    for i in range(grid.shape[0]):\n        for j in range(grid.shape[1]):\n            dots = np.sum(grid[i, j])\n            if dots < min_dots:\n                min_dots = dots\n                min_square = (i, j)\n    return min_square", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    output_grid = np.copy(input_grid)\n    s = ` Find the square s with the fewest colored dots `( output_grid)\n    s1,s2 = ` Delete the dividing line, find the square s1 on the left of square s and the square s2 on the upper left corner`( output_grid)\n    output_grid = ` Surround the top, bottom, left, and right squares of all square s with s1`( output_grid, s,s1)\n    output_grid = ` Surround 